  "prompt": "Is cornflakes and milk good option for breakfast?",
  "response": "Cornflakes with milk can be a quick and convenient breakfast option, but its nutritional value depends on several factors:\n\nPros:\n1. Easy to prepare\n2. Contains some essential nutrients like calcium (from milk)\n3. Low in fat\n4. Provides quick energy\n5. Some brands are fortified with vitamins and minerals\n\nCons:\n1. Often high in sugar\n2. Low in protein\n3. Relatively low in fiber\n4. May not keep you feeling full for long\n\nTo make it a healthier breakfast:\n1. Choose whole grain or low-sugar cornflakes\n2. Add fresh fruits for more nutrients and fiber\n3. Use low-fat or skim milk\n4. Consider adding nuts or seeds for protein\n5. Pair with a protein source like eggs or yogurt\n\nWhile cornflakes can be part of a balanced diet, it's not the most nutritionally complete breakfast option. Variety and balance are key to a healthy morning meal.",
